Typedef Documentation

typedef int(* BSTree_data_cmp_func)(void *data1, void *data2)

type of function to pass to compare data

Parameters:
data1 the first data pointer to be compared
data2 the second data pointer to be compared
Returns:
less than 0 if data1 is less than data2

0 if data1 is equal to data2

greater than 0 if data1 is greater than data2

note if data is a char pointer strcmp() can be passed

typedef void*(* BSTree_data_copy_func)(void **dest, void *src)

type of function to pass to the copy functions

Parameters:
dest pointer to the new data pointer
src the data pointer in the node to be copyed
Returns:
the new new copyed data NULL on error
note: that unfortunatly strcpy() CAN NOT be used here. you need to allocate memory and then use strcpy()
